John Bean Technologies Corporation Key Developments

JBT Corporation Declares Quarterly Dividend for the Second Quarter of 2017, Payable on June 8, 2017
May 15 17
JBT Corporation announced that its Board of Directors has declared a second quarter 2017 cash dividend of $0.10 per share of outstanding common stock. The dividend will be payable on June 8, 2017 to stockholders of record at the close of business on May 25, 2017.


John Bean Technologies Corporation Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Revises Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Second Quarter of 2017
Apr 25 17
John Bean Technologies Corporation announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue of $344.5 million against $267.1 million for the same period a year ago. operating income was $20.5 million against $9.7 million for the same period a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $17.1 million against $7.7 million for the same period a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $17.6 million against $5.2 million for the same period a year ago. Net income was $17.4 million or $0.57 per basic and diluted share against $5.1 million or $0.17 per basic and diluted share for the same period a year ago. Adjusted income from continuing operations was $17.9 million against $10.1 million for the same period of last year. Adjusted diluted earnings per share from continuing operations was $0.59 against $0.34 for the same period of last year. Total adjusted EBITDA was $33.1 million against $25.5 million for the same period of last year. Long-term debt, less current portion was $372.6 million. Cash provided by continuing operating activities was $23.8 million against $0.2 million for the same period of last year. Capital expenditures were $7.9 million against $11.4 million for the same period of last year. 

The company revised earnings guidance for the year 2017. The company expects higher net income, due to lower interest expense. However, with the increased share count, there will be modest EPS dilution. The company now forecasts full-year diluted earnings per share from continuing operations of $2.95 - $3.10. JBT is raising its forecast for organic revenue growth to 4 to 6%, compared with previous guidance of 3 to 5 %, bringing the total revenue growth forecast to 16%, inclusive of 11% growth from acquisitions. The company also expects segment operating margin expansion of 25 to 50 basis points in 2017, compared with the previous guidance of approximately 50 basis points. 

The company estimates second quarter 2017 revenues of approximately $380 million and income from continuing operations of $0.50 per diluted share. Segment operating profit will reflect continued acquisition-related items and a similar product mix to the first quarter.


John Bean Technologies Mulls Acquisitions
Apr 25 17
John Bean Technologies Corporation (NYSE:JBT) is seeking acquisitions. In the first quarter of 2017, John Bean Technologies completed a 2.3 million share equity offering, generating net proceeds of $184 million. Brian Deck, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of John Bean Technologies, said, “The offering strengthens our balance sheet and provides greater flexibility to continue our disciplined, strategically-driven acquisition program.”



